## Affiliation

Permanent residence in [[Sindrel | Sindrel]] requires **house patronage** (`lore/wiki/wiki/sindrel.textile` Politics). There is no long-term "unaffiliated" civil service class.

- **Adjutant** — house patronage, **gold bracelet**; ranks: Meness Recruit–Serjeant; others Caller, Journeyman, Interpreter, Craftsman, … **Default for any native Sindrellian with a job in the city**, including Fulcrum clerks, Wallarch porters, and house staff.
- **Factor** — senior house officer (Prefect, Emissary, Seer, …); enchanted house tattoo instead of or as well as bracelet.
- **Unaffiliated** — **visitors only**: silver bracelet, ≤36-day stay; foreign traders, diplomats, pilgrims, recent arrivals, refugees not yet (or never) patronised. Also criminals off the books — not legitimate city employment.

If the NPC lives and works in Sindrel long-term, assign a **House** and **Adjutant** (or Factor) unless they are explicitly a visitor the party just met.

## Gender picking

Target for **new** quick NPCs: **45% he/him**, **45% she/her**, **10% non-binary**.

Glance at the [lore bridge dashboard](https://obsidianportal-git-sync.onrender.com/) gender counts if unsure — roster is historically male-heavy; **bias she/her and non-binary** when inventing. Still use he/him ~25–35% of improvisations. Do not lecture the table about quotas.

## House cultural tells

- **Oestra** — armour-first, crimson/black/bronze, weapon worn openly, martial bluntness
- **Meness** — white watch-coat, black trim, spotless visibility, lawful watchful bearing
- **Goela** — purple layers, veils or masks, careful or oracular speech
- **Grimbolg** — work-stained but orderly; moss green, brown wool, apron, tools; useful hands
- **Beltus** — black and gold, excessive layers, implies servants or bound entities
- **Mabon** — indigo/grey craft layers, hands free, maker's marks on clasps or belts
- **Lithra** — grey/silver, usekh or throat-piece, composed performance, controlled poise

## Player vs GM

- Quick NPCs are **player-safe** unless the user asks for GM notes.
- Do not reveal unrevealed factions (Anathemist, spy rings, true house ties) in player-facing output.

## Persisting NPCs

Walk-ons stay in chat. If the user says **save**, **persist**, or **add to wiki**, copy `notes/character-template.textile` to `lore/characters/<op_slug>.textile`, fill frontmatter and sections, and omit portal-assigned fields (`op_id`, `op_url`, timestamps).

## Deep canon (only when needed)

- `lore/wiki/wiki/house-*.textile` — Fashion, philosophy, ranks
- `lore/wiki/wiki/sindrel.textile` — GM block for races + Stay Ledger (do not spoil in player output)
- `notes/quick-npc.md` — human-readable cheat sheet (same tables)
